title: For Sale:  Norinco SKS w/ Ammo and Extras
postcontent:
I have a great Norinco SKS from China. It runs through 7.62x39 ammo like champ, very reliable. It has the proper roll marks that indicate it was made and used in China by their military or security forces (you can see these marks in the photos). This makes it more desirable than the SKS model specifically made for export.

It has a clean bore with great rifling (again, check the pictures). It has a nice trigger (for an SKS), which has a two-stage feel and is very predictable. You'll notice in the photos that it has a lot of character, and the stock looks awesome, which is why I bought it. I'm able to get about four inch groups at 50 yards with it, but I'm no sniper, and I've only put a couple hundred rounds through it.

I'm including 320 rounds of 7.62x39. It's 123 grain hollow point ammo from Brown Bear. It runs well in the gun.

You'll also receive a tactical case that fits the length of the gun really well. In addition to that, you'll get a front sight tool for precisely drifting the sight for windage and adjusting it for elevation. title: For Sale:  Ek, Eck Dagger
postcontent:
This a nice Ek Commando dagger manufactured in Richmond VA
If you are a Ek collector you know the history.  
If not look it up
These knives depending upon the model go for 250-300 Typically the plain daggers with either black or green lacing and sheaths sell in this range as they were the most common
This one does not have a box but is it one of the more rare models and has a wooden handle secured to the full shank with three large copper rivets and washers.
This model and the Ek Bowie knife are less common and bring higher prices than the plain black or green para cord wrapped handle ones.
The knife does not appear to have been used or sharpened
As they all are it is sharp as hell
Full grind on one side and half grind on the other
The price is for cash on a meet and greet local pickup
